            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That breaks sites that want to work over both HTTP and HTTPS. Now, if they only wanted anonymous users with no stored state over HTTP, that would make sense, but it's not on Flask to decide that. The cookie itself is still signed and secure from tampering when sent over HTTP. If the site is served over HTTPS only (which it probably should be in 2018), then this flag doesn't really mean anything anyway and the default is still fine."
        },
