            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@ThiefMaster Yes, that is what I referred to when I said you need to apply \"some configuration on the proxy server\". Still, you have to use the ProxyFix middleware for those `X-Forwarded-` headers to be applied to the request object in the app.\r\n\r\n@davidism the secure flag is still useful in 2018. Apps that run only on HTTPS have a rule that redirects any request on HTTP to the same URL on HTTPS, so they continue to accept HTTP requests. The browser will happily send your session cookie on a HTTP request if you don't make it secure. I don't disagree with your assessment, but the `secure` flag in the session cookie still makes sense to be set on HTTPS only apps."
        },
