            "body": "Just for context, I checked a few other frameworks, and they all use the same `secure=false` default as Flask. I'm inclined to not make this change, it will cause unexpected failures that will be difficult to debug for most users.\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\n\r\n- Django: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.0/ref/settings/#session-cookie-secure.\r\n- Pyramid: https://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid/en/latest/api/session.html#pyramid.session.SignedCookieSessionFactory\r\n- aiohttp: https://aiohttp-session.readthedocs.io/en/stable/reference.html#aiohttp_session.AbstractStorage\r\n- bottle: https://bottlepy.org/docs/dev/api.html#bottle.BaseResponse.set_cookie\r\n- express.js: https://github.com/expressjs/session#cookiesecure\r\n- Ruby on Rails: https://www.rubydoc.info/gems/rack/Rack/Session/Abstract/Persisted\r\n\r\nI could not find any framework that defaults the secure flag on session cookies to true. Do you know any?\r\n\r\n"
        },
